-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Redecard, Gerdau and CSN Were Active
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-05-21T21:01:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/brazilian-stock-movers-redecard-gerdau-and-csn-were-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close. Preferred shares
are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index rose 3.8 percent to 56,590.24.  Redecard SA (RDCD3)  (RDCD3 BS),  Brazil ’s No. 2 card-payment
processor, gained 1.8 percent to 30.60 reais, reversing an
earlier decline of as much as 2.3 percent. Shareholders voted to
get another appraisal of  Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4) ’s offer to buy
the remaining stock it doesn’t own for 35 reais a share.  Credit
Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  has 30 days to prepare the second appraisal,
according to the regulatory filing.  Gerdau SA (GGBR4)  (GGBR4 BS), Latin America’s largest steelmaker,
rallied 7.9 percent, the most in nine months, to 16.80 reais.
Ronald Seckelmann, the company’s vice president of finance, said
at an event in  Rio de Janeiro  today that Gerdau isn’t interested
in buying ThyssenKrupp AG’s stake in Brazilian steelmaker Cia.
Siderurgica do Atlantico.  Cia.  Siderurgica Nacional (CSNA3)  SA (CSNA3 BS), Brazil’s third-
largest steelmaker, rose 5.9 percent to 13.91 reais after David Salama, the company’s head of  investor relations , said at an
event in Rio de Janeiro today that demand may increase 5 percent
to 6 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
